# Netlify Redirects File
# ---------------------
# EXPLANATION OF HTML RETURNING 200 FOR /api:
# Because Netlify is a static-file hosting service, it does not execute your Node.js
# backend code ('server.ts') automatically. Thus, the catch-all rule (/* /index.html 200)
# intercepts all your fetch('/api/...') calls and serves the 'index.html' file instead.
#
# HOW TO FIX THIS:
# 1. Host your 'server.ts' backend separately on a Node-capable platform:
#    (e.g., Render, Railway, Fly.io, or Google Cloud Run)
# 2. Uncomment the line below and replace 'https://your-live-backend-url.com' with your actual server URL.
#    This instructs Netlify to act as an API gateway proxy, forwarding `/api/...` calls to your real server.
#
# /api/*  https://your-live-backend-url.com/api/:splat  200

# FALLBACK FOR SPA ROUTING:
# Catch-all rule that lets React handle router paths. Keep this below the API rule!
/*  /index.html  200

